o3 Answer:
Starting with the compound-interest model  
A(t) = P (1 + r / n)^{n t}

Isolate P:

1. Divide both sides by (1 + r / n)^{n t}:
   P = A(t) ÷ (1 + r / n)^{n t}

2. Write it more compactly (or with a negative exponent):
   P =  A(t) / (1 + r/n)^{nt}
     =  A(t) (1 + r/n)^{-nt}

So the principal (the initial amount invested) is  
P =  A(t) / (1 + r/n)^{nt}.

